05/12/2004
ATHENS, Greece -- Greece and Macedonia are due to renew negotiations Monday (6 December) in a bid to solve their longstanding dispute over the constitutional name of Macedonia.
Representatives of the two countries are due to start talks at the UN.
Greece considers the name Macedonia as part of its cultural and historic heritage and objects to its use by its neighbour.
In other news, Greek Prime Minister Costas Karamanlis will pay a formal visit to Moscow, beginning Tuesday.
The aim is to boost bilateral co-operation.
(AFP, NTV - 04/12/04)
